list.title: Who is Arturo Gamboa? Armed man at Kings Day protest fired at by peacekeeper; bystander killed
list.source: The Times of India on MSN.com
list.abstract: During a \"No Kings\" protest in Salt Lake City, a peacekeeper opened fire on a man who raised a rifle toward the crowd, tragically killing a bystander.

list.title: Who was Arturo Gamboa?
list.description: The police took the man with the rifle, who was identified as Arturo Gamboa, 24, into custody and charged him with murder, Chief Brian Redd of the Salt Lake City Police Department said at a news conference on Sunday. The bystander, who was identified by the police as Arthur Folasa Ah Loo, 39, of Utah, died at a hospital.

list.title: What did Gamboa look like when he saw a crowd?
list.description: Gamboa had a look on his face like he was in shock, asking other people what they should do now, Hernandez recalled. Behunin said Gamboa was sitting cross-legged with the crowd, “like he’s like the rest of us taking shelter.” Hernandez told the crowd Gamboa had a gun, then seized his backpack himself.
list.text: ‘This is a rifle!’: Alert bystander spotted the man who had a gun at the S…

list.title: Did Gamboa fire a shot at a crowd of demonstrators?
list.description: The security members took out their guns and yelled to Mr. Gamboa to drop his weapon. Witnesses told the police that Mr. Gamboa had run toward the crowd of demonstrators, according to the affidavit. Mr. Gamboa “did not fire a shot,” Chief Redd said at the news conference.
list.text: 1 Killed in Shooting at a ‘No Kings’ Protest in Salt Lake City

list.title: What happened to AH loo & Gamboa?
list.description: That’s when one of the men dressed in the vests shot three rounds, hitting Gamboa and Ah Loo, said Redd. Gamboa, who police said didn’t have a criminal history, was wounded and treated before being booked into jail. Redd said that the peacekeepers’ actions are also part of the investigation.
list.text: Protester shot and killed at ‘No Kings’ rally in Utah, police say

list.title: Why did Gamboa pull out a rifle?
list.description: Detectives don’t yet know why Gamboa pulled out a rifle or ran from the peacekeepers, but they accused him of creating the dangerous situation that led to Ah Loo’s death. The Associated Press did not immediately find an attorney listed for Gamboa or contact information for his family in public records.
list.text: Protester shot and killed at ‘No Kings’ rally in Utah, police say

list.title: What did police recover from a gunshot wound to Mr Gamboa?
list.description: Demonstrators directed officers to Mr. Gamboa, who was crouched among a small group of people and who had suffered a gunshot wound to his left side. In addition to the rifle, the police recovered a gas mask and a backpack, according to the affidavit.

data.abstract: Arturo Gamboa, 24, was charged with murder after allegedly firing an AR-15-style rifle during the June 14 “No Kings” protest in Salt Lake City, killing bystander Arthur Folasa Ah Loo. The shooting caused chaos among 10,000 protesters. Two others, including peacekeepers, were also detained. The motive behind shooting remains unclear.

Harry and Meghan, who marked their seventh wedding anniversary in May, share son Prince Archie, 6, and daughter Princess Lilibet, 4. “The best,” Meghan captioned her post.
